main event: An unidentified flying object with red and green lights was observed in the sky on April 5, 1957.
interesting points: The object was seen rising slowly until it faded out of view.,The object was observed through binoculars for about 10 minutes.,The reporting officer speculated that the observation might have been caused by a star or planet flickering in the distance.,The sighting was recorded in a Project 10073 record card.,The observation took place at night under clear sky conditions.
sighted object: one white object with red and green lights
